               <scopecontent id="aspace_3204f9f884fcf58dcd7f46c16905488b">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>This folder contains 31 photographic reproductions of inscriptions in books as well as frontispieces and possibly bookplates. The black-and-white photographs are enclosed in a piece of stationery with the following letterhead: "Society of Antiquaries of London, Burlington House, Piccadilly, W." Written on the stationery is a note from W. H. St. John Hope, dated July 6, 1910, and addressed to Rosenheim.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
